{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778982166390,"sessionID":"ses_1cc754bd9ffeuD9IYi2ivYftXO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_I4txeLE50WJ3luXJHOyeFiid","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed locally and committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I added the missing linkage for `GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly` as `part_of GO:0072583 clathrin-dependent endocytosis`, following the pattern already used for related clathrin coat assembly/endocytosis terms and the discussion in this issue.\n+\n+I also added the missing `term_tracker_item` for this issue to the term metadata.\n+\n+Validation passed with `make travis_build` before and after the edit.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated `GO:0072318 clathrin coat disassembly` in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Added `relationship: part_of GO:0072583 ! clathrin-dependent endocytosis`\n+- Added `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31981\" xsd:anyURI`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a missing superclass, but the issue discussion clarified that the appropriate modeling here is `part_of`, not an additional `is_a`.\n+- Existing ontology precedent supports this pattern: `GO:0099049 clathrin coat assembly involved in endocytosis` is modeled as `part_of GO:0072583`.\n+- `GO:0072318` already has a suitable asserted parent (`is_a: GO:0072319 ! vesicle uncoating`) plus a logical definition for clathrin coat disassembly, so adding another `is_a` would be unnecessary and likely over-assertive.\n+\n+Process followed:\n+\n+- Reviewed issue title, body, and comments from `__issue_context__.json`\n+- Checked relevant terms and neighboring modeling in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- Consulted design-pattern guidance to avoid adding unnecessary logical axioms\n+- Checked out `GO:0072318` with `